      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's an interesting distinction. When you say a \"diverse, dynamic energy\" might be seen as \"unrefined\" or \"common\" compared to \"tradition,\" are you saying that certain types of cultural expression are inherently less sophisticated? Like, if a neighborhood is predominantly composed of immigrant communities or people of color, does that automatically push it into that \"unrefined\" category in the eyes of luxury buyers?",
